---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
const title = "About | Cassady Tech Solutions";
const description = "About Cassady Tech Solutions and its security-focused managed IT support for small to mid-sized businesses in Southern Colorado.";
---
<SiteLayout title={title} description={description} active="about">
	<section class="page-title"><div class="section-inner"><p class="eyebrow">About</p><h1>Managed IT with a local sense of proportion.</h1><p>Cassady Tech Solutions supports small to mid-sized organizations that need dependable service, honest recommendations, and systems that make sense at their size.</p></div></section>
	<section class="section"><div class="section-inner grid two"><div class="content-block"><h2>Practical before flashy.</h2><p>Growing organizations often inherit a mix of computers, accounts, routers, websites, spreadsheets, vendors, and cloud subscriptions. The goal is not to make everything complicated. The goal is to make the essentials understandable, recoverable, and easier to maintain.</p><p>Cassady Tech Solutions focuses on proactive IT operations, right-sized security practices, operational continuity, and documentation that keeps critical technology knowledge accessible.</p></div><div class="ops-panel"><div class="status-strip"><span class="status-dot"></span><div><strong>Support style</strong><span>Plain language, steady process, realistic next steps.</span></div><span>Focused</span></div><div class="metric-grid"><div class="metric-card"><strong>Fit</strong><span>Small to mid-sized organizations that need practical technical coverage.</span></div><div class="metric-card"><strong>Focus</strong><span>Reliable systems, clean access, backup awareness, and better documentation.</span></div></div></div></div></section>
	<section class="section alt"><div class="section-inner"><div class="section-heading"><p class="eyebrow">Working principles</p><h2>Good support should leave things clearer than it found them.</h2></div><div class="grid three"><article class="value-card"><h3>Stability first</h3><p>When something is blocking work, stabilize the system before chasing nice-to-have improvements.</p></article><article class="value-card"><h3>Document the useful parts</h3><p>Support notes, account maps, vendor context, and simple checklists make future problems faster to solve.</p></article><article class="value-card"><h3>Respect risk</h3><p>Security, backups, and account access should be handled carefully, even when the setup is lean.</p></article></div></div></section>
</SiteLayout>
